        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 31 at 5:36PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 536 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southwest of Mertzon, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Mertzon and Sherwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
